Objective: Create a Virtual machine scale in Azure with a Linux image using the Azure cli
Image to be used: Ubuntu 22.04 LTS

Prerequisites:
1. Azure CLI installed (`az version` to check)
2. az login
3. az account set --subscription "<your-subscription-id>"
4. Or you can use shell.azure.com and use your cloud shell as well.

Step 1: Create a Resource Group
Bash - az group create \
  --name myResourceGroup \
  --location eastus

Step 2: Create the Linux VMSS
Bash - az vmss create \
  --resource-group myResourceGroup \
  --name myScaleSet \
  --image Ubuntu2204 \
  --upgrade-policy-mode automatic \
  --admin-username azureuser \
  --generate-ssh-keys \
  --instance-count 2 \
  --vm-sku Standard_B2s

Step 3: Check the Deployment
az vmss list --resource-group myResourceGroup -o table

To see individual instances:
az vmss list-instances \
  --resource-group myResourceGroup \
  --name myScaleSet \
  -o table

Step 4: Connect to a VM Instance
First, get the public IP of the load balancer:
az network public-ip list \
  --resource-group myResourceGroup \
  -o table

Then connect (replace `<public-ip>` and `<port>`):
ssh azureuser@<public-ip> -p <port>

Step 5: Clean Up (optional)
az group delete --name myResourceGroup --yes --no-wait

